LIST.NAME: Bitcoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Bitcoin is a decentralized cryptocurrency that records transactions using blockchain and P2P technology. Verified by miners with a total supply limited to 21 million BTC. Bitcoin is used for transactions, store of value, or investment.

LIST.NAME: Ethereum
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Ethereum: a decentralized platform for smart contracts, apps and transactions using Ether. ETH is used for payments, store of value and collateral. Valuable for decentralized finance, NFTs and applications.

LIST.NAME: Solana
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Solana (SOL) is a high-performance blockchain using dPoS and a unique transaction ordering to process over 50,000 transactions per second. Native SOL token used for transaction fees and smart contracts.

LIST.NAME: Sui
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Sui is a decentralized Layer 1 blockchain, integrating the Move language for enhanced composability. Developed by Mysten Labs, led by Evan Cheng, its SUI token manages gas fees, staking, and aligns incentives in its delegated Proof-of-Stake system.

LIST.NAME: Arbitrum
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Arbitrum is a protocol for faster, cheaper Ethereum transactions with ARB governance token enabling decentralized governance via the Security Council and Arbitrum DAO.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: When calculating Market Capitalization (market cap), we account for all coins in circulation, including those held by team members or the company. This also includes coins in smart contracts or escrow. If the coins have been issued and have not been burned, they will be accounted for in the market cap.
LIST.NAME: XRP
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: XRP is a fast and green native token of the XRP Ledger, designed for financial services. Ripple promotes XRP use via RippleNet, offering connections to financial institutions worldwide for cross-border transactions.

LIST.NAME: TRON
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The TRX token has a number of use cases, with the main one being to pay transaction fees on the Tron blockchain. Holders can boost their earnings by staking tokens with a Super Representative on the network by freezing their tokens.

LIST.NAME: Celestia
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $TIA, serves multiple pivotal roles within the network. It's used to pay for data space, bootstrap new rollups without the immediate need to issue a new token, secure the network through a proof-of-stake mechanism built on the Cosmos SDK

LIST.NAME: Ethereum Classic
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Ethereum Classic (ETC) is a decentralized blockchain platform for dApps, tokens, and value exchange. Created in 2016, ETC prioritizes immutability and censorship-resistance, making it ideal for secure and decentralized projects.

LIST.NAME: Aptos
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: APT is the native currency of the Aptos blockchain, which uses AptosBFT consensus protocol for safety and liveness. Mainnet launched in October 2022 with 1 billion tokens and 8 digits of precision. Minimal unit is called an Octa.

LIST.NAME: Avalanche
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Avalanche (AVAX) is a 2020 blockchain platform optimized for fast transactions and DeFi applications. It's secure, Ethereum-compatible, and features a multi-purpose AVAX token.

LIST.NAME: Litecoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Litecoin (LTC), a Bitcoin fork created in 2011, offers fast, low-fee transactions. Its decentralized ledger supports a larger supply of 84 million coins, mined via Proof-of-Work, ensuring transparent, controlled inflation.

LIST.NAME: Binance Coin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: BNB, created by Changpeng Zhao, is integral to the Binance ecosystem, serving as a versatile utility token within and outside of the Binance platform.

LIST.NAME: Cardano
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Cardano (ADA) is a Proof-of-Stake blockchain enabling dApps, tokens, and more. Uses Ouroboros consensus mechanism for staking pools. Launched in 2017, maintained by three organizations and its community. ADA used for fees, governance, and rewards.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: Sei (SEI) token is not live yet
LIST.NAME: Sei
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The Sei network's primary cryptocurrency is SEI, it's utilized for a range of functions within the Sei network. This includes the payment of fees, staking, and involvement in governance processes

LIST.NAME: Dogecoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Dogecoin (DOGE) is a meme-inspired cryptocurrency with a large supply. Created as a joke in 2013, but gained value from demand, now accepted by large retailers. Gained value from potential adoption by Elon Musk's companies.

LIST.NAME: Polygon
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Polygon (MATIC) is an Ethereum scaling solution. A parallel blockchain that users can bridge their tokens to and interact with through compatible wallets. Secured by a Proof-of-Stake consensus, MATIC is used for fees and staking rewards.

LIST.NAME: Optimism
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Optimism is a layer-two platform on Ethereum that uses "optimistic rollups". It enables low-cost, near-instantaneous transactions, used to develop financial apps, social networks, games, etc.

LIST.NAME: Bitcoin Cash
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Bitcoin Cash (BCH) is a decentralized cryptocurrency created in 2017 by modifying the Bitcoin protocol. It has larger blocks for faster, cheaper transactions and is gaining popularity among merchants and businesses worldwide.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: This page refers to the mainnet token that [went live](https://filecoin.io/blog/mainnet-liftoff/#:~:text=The%20Filecoin%20network%20represents%20a,stored%20and%20replicated%20over%20time.) on October 15, 2020
LIST.NAME: FileCoin
Internet Computer
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The Internet Computer (ICP) token fuels the Internet Computer protocol, used for transaction fees, access to services, and rewarding network contributors. A deflationary token with a fixed supply, it's anticipated to increase in value over time.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: This page refers to the new DOT which is 100x smaller than the old DOT (the DOT token underwent a redenomination from its original sale on 21 August 2020 at 16:40 UTC, block number 1,248,328)
LIST.NAME: Polkadot
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: DOT is the currency of the Polkadot network, enabling staking, governance, transactions, parachain auctions, and bonding for a multi-chain ecosystem with interoperability.

LIST.NAME: Injective Protocol
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Injective Protocol (INJ) is the native staking token. Staked holders can govern and decide the future of the protocol. INJ is an ERC-20 token

LIST.NAME: Near
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: NEAR token is a digital asset in the NEAR ecosystem for paying transaction fees, staking, and governance. It enables economic coordination among network participants and new behaviors for network applications.

LIST.NAME: EOS
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: EOS is a decentralized platform for dApps, solving scalability and usability issues. EOSIO blockchain powers EOS token used for transaction fees and governance. Created by Dan Larimer, founder of Bitshares, Steem, and Block.one.

LIST.NAME: Terra
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Terra, an open-source blockchain with dApps and advanced tools, uses proof-of-stake. After UST's crash, Terra Classic's Proposal 1623 led to a new chain and Luna airdrop. Luna and UST collapsed post-depegging.

LIST.NAME: Cosmos
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: ATOM, the Cosmos Network's cryptocurrency, facilitates transactions and staking, securing the ecosystem. It incentivizes participants through staking rewards and empowers users in network governance decisions.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: Please note that RUNE token runs on 3 different chains: Mainnet, BEP2 and ERC20. Both BEP2 and ERC20 can be swapped to the native token (mainnet) on a 1:1 basis. Only the native RUNE has a use-case within THORChain. The total combined supply is 500m. Check this description page to find the three respective block explorers.
LIST.NAME: Thorchain
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: RUNE is the native token of Thorchain, used for exchange, network security, governance, decision-making, and liquidity provision rewards.

LIST.NAME: Monero
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Monero (XMR) is a decentralized cryptocurrency created in April 2014 by a group of developers led by the pseudonymous developer "thankful_for_today".

LIST.NAME: Bitcoin SV
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Bitcoin SV (BSV) resulted from a 2018 Bitcoin Cash fork. It seeks to restore Satoshi's vision, scale blockchain, ensure stability & security. BSV faces controversy due to Craig Wright's unproven claims as Bitcoin creator.

LIST.NAME: Chiliz
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Chiliz (CHZ) is a utility token for the Chiliz blockchain used to power Socios.com. It enables buying/trading of Fan Tokens for exclusive rewards, and pays for transaction fees.

LIST.NAME: Flow
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Flow is a blockchain network created by Dapper Labs for digital collectibles and blockchain-based games. Its native token is FLOW, which is used for transaction fees, staking, and storage.

LIST.NAME: Hedera Hashgraph
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Hedera Hashgraph, led by Dr. Leemon Baird & Mance Harmon, is an open-source network using HBAR, an efficient cryptocurrency. It supports 10,000 transactions/sec at ~$0.0001 USD. Staking offers up to 6.5% APY. Founders contribute from Swirlds Labs.

LIST.NAME: ZCash
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: ZEC is a digital currency and decentralized open-source cryptocurrency, launched in 2016. It provides users with enhanced privacy and selective transparency of transactions. ZCash is based on the zero-knowledge proof protocol known as zk-SNARKs.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: Following the recent de-pegging incident of UST, Luna and UST are experiencing high volatility in volume and price. Check Luna's [official twitter page](https://twitter.com/terra_money) to stay updated.
LIST.NAME: Terra Classic
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: LUNC, formerly Luna, is Terra blockchain's original token, renamed Terra Classic post-UST depegging. It's the native staking asset of Terra Classic, securing its PoS system and aiding governance, despite a new Terra chain.

LIST.NAME: Stacks
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Stacks (STX) is the native token of the Stacks blockchain, a layer-one blockchain built on top of Bitcoin. It enables developers to create dApps with smart contracts, tokenize assets and build digital marketplaces.

LIST.NAME: Neutron
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The Neutron (NTRN) token functions within the ecosystem of the Neutron platform. It plays a crucial role in the platform’s operations, particularly in the token generation event and auction process.

LIST.NAME: Fetch.AI
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The FET token is an essential component of the Fetch.AI ecosystem, operating as the primary medium of exchange. It's used to pay for transactions, services, and access to additional functionalities within the platform.

LIST.NAME: Stellar Lumen
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Lumen (XLM) is the digital asset used to denominate network requirements in the Stellar network. It acts as a medium of exchange between illiquid assets and is required for minimum balance and transaction fees.

LIST.NAME: The Open Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The Open Network (TON) utilizes its native cryptocurrency known as TON Crystal. This decentralized token is based on the TON blockchain and plays a vital role in the functioning and governance of the entire network

LIST.NAME: Astar
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: ASTR token powers dApps, DeFi, NFTs on Astar (ASTR) blockchain. Used for fees, governance, staking. Enables cross-chain interoperability, fostering innovation in blockchain space.

LIST.NAME: Fantom
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Fantom (FTM) is a fast, DAG-based blockchain with FTM tokens for staking, governance, and fees, enabling near-instant transactions at negligible costs.

LIST.NAME: Mina Protocol
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: MINA tokens power Mina Protocol, used for governance, transaction fees, staking, and consensus. Enable privacy, security, and scalability for dApps on the Mina blockchain.

LIST.NAME: BitTorrent
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: BitTorrent Token (BTT) is a cryptocurrency developed for use in the BitTorrent peer-to-peer file-sharing network. The token is a TRC-10 utility token based on the TRON blockchain.

LIST.NAME: Core
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The CORE token serves several purposes. Firstly, it serves as the native token of the Core blockchain, allowing users to pay for transactions, interact with smart contracts, and participate in governance decisions

LIST.NAME: Arweave
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Arweave (AR) is a decentralized network offering immutable, permanent data storage via its unique "blockweave" blockchain. Its native AR token facilitates storage payments, staking, voting, and marketplace transactions.

LIST.NAME: TOP Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: TOP Network: An infrastructure for DApps and smart contracts, boasting high speed, low fees, and diverse applications. Includes decentralized communication for added utility.

LIST.NAME: Algorand
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Algorand (ALGO) is primarily used as a means of payment and a store of value. It is used to transfer money, purchase goods and services, and send messages securely.

LIST.NAME: Oasis Labs
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The ROSE token is used for transaction fees on the Oasis network and as a means of exchange on cryptocurrency exchanges. It can also be used for staking and potentially have governance functions as the network matures.

LIST.NAME: Livepeer
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: LPT is the native cryptocurrency of the Livepeer network. It plays an integral role in the protocol by incentivizing and ensuring the trustworthiness of participating nodes in the decentralized video streaming network

LIST.NAME: Step App
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Step App (FITFI) is the governance token of the Step App Network, which benefits from ecosystem fees. The platform also has an in-game token, KCAL, used to mint and maintain SNEAK (non-fungible tokens) and Step App features

LIST.NAME: Xinfin Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $XDC is the utility token of XinFin Network, it serves as the underlying settlement mechanism for DApps built on the XinFin network. With XDC, users can facilitate transactions, access services, and participate in the XinFin ecosystem.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: In September 2022, Ethereum is scheduled to start ETH 2.0's Merge upgrade. Some exchanges will support its potential hard fork. If successful, the Merge could create two parallel blockchains after the upgrade.
LIST.NAME: EthereumPoW
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: ETHW is a PoW-based token created from Ethereum's hard fork. Tradable on several exchanges; claim using Metamask wallet on the ETHPoW network. ETHW has a different inflation rate than Ethereum on PoS.

LIST.NAME: Tezos
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Tezos is a self-upgradable, proof-of-stake blockchain enabling secure asset and application hosting. Users contribute via 'baking' or delegation. Created by Arthur and Kathleen Breitman, it's crafted for enhanced security through formal verification.

LIST.NAME: Conflux Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The CFX token is used for staking, transaction fees, and as a store of value. Staking CFX provides network security, governance rights, and rewards. CFX is also used for paying transaction fees on the network and can be held as a store of value.

LIST.NAME: Celo
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: CELO is the native token of the Celo blockchain platform, primarily used for staking, governance, and as a means of exchange for services and products within the Celo ecosystem.

LIST.NAME: NEO
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: NEO (NEO) is used to build dApps and smart contracts on the NEO blockchain, as well as a means of payment and a store of value. Additionally, NEO generates GAS, used for transaction fees and computational resources on the network.

LIST.NAME: Dash
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Dash (DASH) is a decentralized digital currency launched in 2014. It prioritizes fast, secure, and private transactions with additional services. DASH is used for payments, remittances, and investing. It was created by Evan Duffield.

LIST.NAME: TerraClassicUSD
Kaspa
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Kaspa (KAS) employs blockDAG for scalable, secure transactions. GHOSTDAG ensures fast confirms. It boasts DAG queries, block pruning, SPV proofs, and Layer 2 visions. With a 28.7B cap, its launch had no pre-mining, emphasizing equitable distribution.

LIST.NAME: Kusama
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: KSM is the native token of the Kusama blockchain. It serves as the primary means of participating in the network's governance, as well as being used as a form of collateral for validators who provide security to the network.

LIST.NAME: Kadena
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The KDA token is the native cryptocurrency of the Kadena platform. It serves as a digital currency used for transaction fees and compute payments on the Kadena public chain. It is a POW asset and it uses Blake2S mining algorithm

LIST.NAME: Waves
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Waves is a blockchain protocol created in 2016 by Sasha Ivanov. It provides backend support for Web 3.0 services, with purpose-built tools for easy dApp development. Its technology addresses the security, reliability, and speed of IT systems.

LIST.NAME: Chia
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: XCH is a digital asset designed to be used within the Chia ecosystem. It's the compensation for participants, known as "farmers", who help in securing the network by allocating their unused disk space for network use

LIST.NAME: Creditcoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The CTC token powers the Creditcoin network for digital commerce transactions, settlement, and trading. It also has potential governance functions as the network matures, creating a decentralized marketplace for digital assets.

LIST.NAME: Polymesh
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: POLYX is the native utility token of the Polymesh blockchain, a specialized blockchain platform designed explicitly for security tokens. POLYX is utilized for various purposes within the Polymesh ecosystem, including transaction fees and staking

LIST.NAME: Theta Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Theta Network is a blockchain infrastructure for media and entertainment industries with a dual token system. THETA is the governance token and TFUEL is the operational token. It helps existing media platforms reduce costs and generate revenues.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE:
**[Elrond (ERD) to Elrond (EGLD) swap:](https://elrond.com/blog/the-elrond-token-swap-begins-on-the-3rd-of-september/)**

Following the launch of the Elrond Mainnet on the 30th of July, Elrond officially began the token swap from ERD to EGLD on the 3rd of September of 2020. The eGLD ticker is an abbreviation for eGold, denoting the metaphor of what the Elrond currency aims to become. Elrond's dedicated website [Elrond Bridge](https://bridge.elrond.com/erd/#/) enabled ERC20/BEP2 ERD holders to swap their tokens for eGLD at a 1000:1 ratio (1000 ERD (old) = 1 eGLD (new)).
LIST.NAME: MultiversX
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: MultiversX offers scalable blockchain, secure dApps, state sharding, & diverse app dev via a virtual machine. Roles: Validator, Observer, Fisherman. Native token: eGold (EGLD). Founded 2017, switched from ERD to EGLD in 2020.

LIST.NAME: Huobi Token
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: HT is primarily used for paying trading fees on the Huobi exchange. Holders enjoy fee discounts, access to events, and voting rights. Huobi buys back and burns HT, reducing supply and potentially increasing value.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: Due to the VeChain renaming and price scaling in July/August 2018, prices prior to those dates represent the price of the original token which was equal to 100x VET.
LIST.NAME: VeChain
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: VeChain (VET) is VeChainThor blockchain's heart. Beyond transactions, it fuels the network. VET holders can vote, partake in PoA, and gain VTHO. They can also stake and trade. VeChainThor, propelled by VET, seeks blockchain prominence.

LIST.NAME: QTUM
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: QTUM token is the native cryptocurrency of the QTUM blockchain. Users who hold QTUM tokens can participate in the staking process, which allows them to earn rewards for validating transactions on the blockchain.

LIST.NAME: Horizen
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The ZEN token itself is a mineable cryptocurrency that uses a Proof of Work (PoW) consensus algorithm similar to Bitcoin, but with an altered block reward allocation. ZEN can be held, transacted, or used as fees in the Horizen ecosystem.

LIST.NAME: Zilliqa
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Zilliqa is a fast, secure, and cost-effective blockchain that uses sharding and pBFT consensus for security. It has Scilla, a safety-focused language for smart contracts and was created by researchers from the National University of Singapore

LIST.NAME: Klaytn
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $KLAY is the native cryptocurrency of the Klaytn blockchain platform. It serves as a utility token, used for various purposes in the ecosystem. $KLAY is used for transaction fees, providing an incentive for validators and securing the network.

LIST.NAME: Ontology Gas
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $ONG is the utility token of the Ontology network functioning in a dual-token system alongside the Ontology (ONT) token. $ONG is used for transactions, operations on the Ontology blockchain. Used for transaction fees, execute smart contracts an more

LIST.NAME: Acala
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Acala (ACA) is the native utility token of the Acala Network, functioning as its primary means of governance, staking, and utility within the ecosystem

LIST.NAME: ABBC Coin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: ABBC Coin (ABBC) is the native cryptocurrency of the ABBC Coin platform. It is primarily used as a means of payment for products and services offered by the platform, as well as to incentivize network participation and reward node operators.

LIST.NAME: Arkham
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The ARKM token is used for several purposes within the Arkham platform. It serves as the currency of the Arkham Intel Exchange. Token holders are also entitled to governance rights to vote on the strategic direction of Arkham.

LIST.NAME: Kava
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The KAVA token is integral to the security, governance, and mechanical functions of the Kava platform.

LIST.NAME: Reef
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Reef is a DeFi platform with a cross-chain liquidity aggregator and yield engine, supporting Ethereum, Binance Smart Chain, and Polkadot. The native utility token, REEF, enables fee payments, on-chain governance, and collateral within the ecosystem.

LIST.NAME: aelf
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: aelf (ELF) is an ERC-20-based token that operates on the Ethereum platform. It is utilized as the primary token within the aelf ecosystem and plays a significant role in its functioning, as discussed below.

LIST.NAME: IOS token
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: IOST serves as the native utility token of the IOST ecosystem. It is used for various purposes, including staking and voting for block producers, accessing and utilizing dApps on the IOST network, and paying for transaction fees and network services

LIST.NAME: NEM
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: NEM's native currency, XEM, is used for transaction fees on the network and incentivizes the nodes that maintain the blockchain.

LIST.NAME: Siacoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Siacoin (SC) powers the Sia network, a decentralized cloud storage platform. SC is used to rent storage, with smart contracts ensuring secure transactions. Sia and Siacoin (SC) were created by Skynet Labs' founders.

LIST.NAME: Helium
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $HNT is the native crypto of the Helium Network. It serves as an incentive and a reward for individuals who contribute to the network with Hotspots. These Hotspots offer network coverage and mine $HNT through an algorithm called "Proof-of-Coverage

LIST.NAME: Flare
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Flare Network's token, FLR, is integral to network security, governance, and data reliability. It incentivizes adoption of the Flare Time Series Oracle (FTSO), is used as stake by data providers, and facilitates transactions.

LIST.NAME: Osmosis
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The OSMO token is the governance token for Osmosis. It empowers token holders to actively participate in the evolution of the protocol. It is a proof-of-stake cryptocurrency and it does not have a fixed maximum supply.

LIST.NAME: IOTA
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The IOTA token is the native digital currency for the IOTA DLT protocol. It leverages a unique "Tangle" structure for improved scalability and speed. Managed by the IOTA mainnet, the token supports decentralized data and asset control.

LIST.NAME: Cortex
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The CTXC token functions as a 'gas' or utility token within the Cortex platform, and is necessary for performing various activities. It is used to reward miners, validate transactions, and participate in the creation and utilization of AI models.

LIST.NAME: Moonbeam
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The GLMR token is an ERC-20 token that serves as the native currency of the Glimmer (GLMR) project. It is used to incentivize users to participate in the Glimmer network and to reward them for contributing to the project.

LIST.NAME: Ravencoin
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Ravencoin is a decentralized blockchain launched in 2018 without an ICO or pre-mine. It uses the X16R algorithm for mining and has since moved to KAWPOW. Created by Bruce Fenton, it's energy-efficient and resistant to ASIC domination.

LIST.NAME: WEMIX
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: $WEMIX is the native token of the WEMIX3.0 ecosystem and serves several important functions. It is used for staking, which is a prerequisite for becoming an authority member.

LIST.NAME: Casper Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Casper Network (CSPR) token is used for staking, transaction fees, governance, and consensus. It incentivizes node operators, secures the network, and allows token holders to participate in decision-making processes.

LIST.NAME: Harmony
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The ONE token is an integral part of this network, used for various purposes like transaction fees, staking, and governance.

LIST.NAME: MAP Protocol
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: MAP Protocol is a Bitcoin layer-2, P2P omnichain network enabling cross-chain interoperability. It uses a decentralized approach for secure, decentralized blockchain communication and transactions.

LIST.NAME: IoTeX Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The IOTX token is used for transactions, staking, governance, and registering new devices on the network. The IoTeX ecosystem includes projects such as Ucam, Pebble, Mimo DEX, and IoTeX Scout, among others.

LIST.NAME: Cronos
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: Founded in 2016, Crypto.com offers crypto trading, storage, a mobile app, and a Visa card. It features its EVM, CronosScan, and native token, Cronos (CRO). The platform rebranded in 2018 following a domain purchase.

LIST.NAME: DeFiChain
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The DFI token itself is an integral component of the DeFiChain ecosystem. It is used for transaction fees and serves as the primary asset for staking and liquidity mining on the platform.

LIST.NAME: Boba Network
LIST.ASSET_DESCRIPTION_SNIPPET: The BOBA token is the native utility token of the Boba Network. It is primarily used to facilitate various activities within the ecosystem, such as paying transaction fees, staking, and participating in governance decisions.

LIST.PUBLIC_NOTICE: **[Zelcash (ZEL)](https://www.cryptocompare.com/coins/zel/overview/BTC)** has been **[rebranded](https://fluxofficial.medium.com/zel-flux-network-upgrade-streamlined-defi-access-4710a447c3ac)** to Flux (FLUX).
